&lt;p&gt;Royal Free London NHS Foundation TrustSenior Clinical Fellow in Oral &amp; Maxillofacial Surgery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applications are invited to apply for a 12-month fixed term post as a Senior Clinical Fellow in Oral &amp; Maxillofacial Surgery. Applicants should be dual-qualified (medical and dental). This position offers the successful candidate the opportunity to join an established department dealing with all aspects of Oral &amp; Maxillofacial Surgery and Thyroid Surgery with established referral patterns. The department at The Royal Free London NHS Foundation Trust is run by 5 Consultant Maxillofacial Surgeons and 3 Consultant Orthodontists.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This post is based at Chase Farm and Barnet Hospitals with satellite clinics at the Royal Free and Edgware Community Hospitals. Adult elective surgery is centralised to a dedicated theatre at Chase Farm with paediatric surgery at Barnet Hospital. The on-call service and emergency service is based at Barnet Hospital where the first tier of on call consists of nine junior staff (6 DF1/2 and 3 Trust Doctors) on a compliant 48hr full shift rota with 1 in 6 middle tier nights and a weekend middle grade non-resident on-call cover based at Barnet Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note - this post falls under the 2002 Hospital Medical and Dental staff terms and conditions, with the salary on the MN37 pay scale. It is a trust grade role, not a recognised training post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Deepak Komath&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Consultant Maxillofacial Surgeon, Clinical Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: deepak.komath@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
